  "name": "TEMA ADX Trend Confirmation",
  "description": "This expert-level Trend Following algorithm utilizes a confluence of Triple Exponential Moving Average (TEMA) crossovers and the Average Directional Movement Index (ADX) to confirm trend strength. It enters long positions when the fast TEMA crosses above the slow TEMA while the ADX is above 25, indicating a strong uptrend.",
  "algorithm_type": "TrendFollowing",
  "prompt": "Create an expert-level TrendFollowing trading algorithm in Pine Script designed for the 1-hour timeframe that uses a confluence of a Triple Exponential Moving Average (TEMA) crossover and the Average Directional Movement Index (ADX) above 25 to confirm trend strength. The strategy should enter a long position when the fast TEMA (length 9) crosses above the slow TEMA (length 21) and ADX(14) confirms trend strength by being above 25, with volume increasing above its 20-period simple moving average to filter out low-volume signals. Exit long positions when the fast TEMA crosses below the slow TEMA or ADX falls below 20. Similarly, generate short entries when the fast TEMA crosses below the slow TEMA with ADX above 25 and volume above its 20 SMA, exiting when the crossover reverses or ADX dips below 20. Include stop-loss and take-profit parameters based on 1.5x and 3x the current Average True Range (ATR 14). Provide clear buy/sell signal markers and position size management based on a fixed percentage of equity.",
